<subSubSection lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1870,2041]" box="[151,1089,1870,1897]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1870,1896]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A pair of processes on male abdominal sternite VI convergent (
<figureCitation box="[986,1076,1871,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 9O</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1870,2041]" lastBlockId="40.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,535,1906,1932]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Supplementary description.</emphasis>
Supracervical setae 5–10 per side. Eye with stout, dense interfacetal setulae. Cibarial, medial sensilla approximately 3 per side; posterior sensillum 0–1 per side (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1225,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,798,822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[151,1435,181,774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Characters 5 and 6 on the cibarium (dorsal view) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. cristata de Meijere (B) and C. sarawakana sp. nov. (C). Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensillum; s c, sensilla campaniformia. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766410/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Supralateral seta outside prementum 0–1 per side (
<figureCitation box="[538,645,1979,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1178,1202]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 26. Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Menglun, Xishuangbanna,Yunnan, China).A, Dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view); B, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766458/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). Prescutellar acrostichal setae present; acrostichal setulae in 4 rows. Apical scutellar setae nearly equidistant from each other and from basal scutellar seta. Costal setae in middle row all apically blunt, heavy, peg-like (
<figureCitation box="[550,643,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[286,1299,181,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[286,1300,181,1927]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Character 12 of costal setae on the wing (anterodistal portion) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. colocasiae (Duda) (B) and C. cristata de Meijere (C). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766414/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Mid tibia with approximately 3 apical, stout setae. Male abdominal sternites III and IV longer than wide, posteriorly slightly narrowing (
<figureCitation box="[933,1037,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1178,1202]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 26. Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Menglun, Xishuangbanna,Yunnan, China).A, Dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view); B, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766458/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 26B</figureCitation>
). Female abdominal sternites VI as wide as long, posteriorly dilated, medially notched on posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[954,1057,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1178,1202]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 26. Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Menglun, Xishuangbanna,Yunnan, China).A, Dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view); B, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766458/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 26C</figureCitation>
). Epandrium pubescent except for anterior margin and anteroventral elongation, posteroventrally prominently extended, with approximately 1 seta on lateral portion and 11–12 setae on posteroventral portion of each side (
<figureCitation box="[943,1043,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
). Surstylus long, narrow plate with 3 recurved teeth apically and 1 minute seta subapically (
<figureCitation box="[784,889,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 10H</figureCitation>
). Median piece of subepandrial sclerite medially and anteriorly bilobed into long lobes; lateral pieces long, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[901,1006,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 10G</figureCitation>
). Cercus pubescent except for anterior margin and ventral 1/3, with approximately 30 setae (
<figureCitation box="[746,845,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
). Oviscapt about 8 times as long as wide, with 16–17 ovisensilla (
<figureCitation box="[286,391,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1178,1202]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[151,1435,181,1154]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 26. Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Menglun, Xishuangbanna,Yunnan, China).A, Dorsal portion of proboscis (caudal view); B, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766458/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 26D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
